snippets.title: cloudkms CreateEkmConnection Sample
snippets.description:
CreateEkmConnection creates a new EkmConnection in a given
Project and Location.

snippets.title: cloudkms GetEkmConnection Sample
snippets.description:
GetEkmConnection returns metadata for a given
EkmConnection.

snippets.title: cloudkms GetIamPolicy Sample
snippets.description:
GetIamPolicy gets the access control policy for a resource. Returns an empty policy
if the resource exists and does not have a policy set.

snippets.title: cloudkms GetLocation Sample
snippets.description: GetLocation gets information about a location.

snippets.title: cloudkms ListEkmConnections Sample
snippets.description: ListEkmConnections lists EkmConnections.

snippets.title: cloudkms ListLocations Sample
snippets.description: ListLocations lists information about the supported locations for this service.

snippets.title: cloudkms SetIamPolicy Sample
snippets.description:
SetIamPolicy sets the access control policy on the specified resource. Replaces
any existing policy.

Can return NOT_FOUND, INVALID_ARGUMENT, and PERMISSION_DENIED
errors.

snippets.title: cloudkms TestIamPermissions Sample
snippets.description:
TestIamPermissions returns permissions that a caller has on the specified resource. If the
resource does not exist, this will return an empty set of
permissions, not a NOT_FOUND error.

Note: This operation is designed to be used for building
permission-aware UIs and command-line tools, not for authorization
checking. This operation may “fail open” without warning.

snippets.title: cloudkms UpdateEkmConnection Sample
snippets.description: UpdateEkmConnection updates an EkmConnection's metadata.

snippets.title: cloudkms AsymmetricDecrypt Sample
snippets.description:
AsymmetricDecrypt decrypts data that was encrypted with a public key retrieved from
GetPublicKey
corresponding to a CryptoKeyVersion
with CryptoKey.purpose
ASYMMETRIC_DECRYPT.

snippets.title: cloudkms AsymmetricSign Sample
snippets.description:
AsymmetricSign signs data using a CryptoKeyVersion
with CryptoKey.purpose
ASYMMETRIC_SIGN, producing a signature that can be verified with the public
key retrieved from
GetPublicKey.

snippets.title: cloudkms CreateCryptoKey Sample
snippets.description:
CreateCryptoKey create a new CryptoKey within a
KeyRing.

CryptoKey.purpose and
CryptoKey.version_template.algorithm
are required.

snippets.title: cloudkms CreateCryptoKeyVersion Sample
snippets.description:
CreateCryptoKeyVersion create a new CryptoKeyVersion in a
CryptoKey.

The server will assign the next sequential id. If unset,
state will be set to
ENABLED.

snippets.title: cloudkms CreateImportJob Sample
snippets.description:
CreateImportJob create a new ImportJob within a
KeyRing.

ImportJob.import_method is
required.

snippets.title: cloudkms CreateKeyRing Sample
snippets.description:
CreateKeyRing create a new KeyRing in a given Project and
Location.

snippets.title: cloudkms Decrypt Sample
snippets.description:
Decrypt decrypts data that was protected by
Encrypt. The
CryptoKey.purpose must be
ENCRYPT_DECRYPT.

snippets.title: cloudkms DestroyCryptoKeyVersion Sample
snippets.description:
DestroyCryptoKeyVersion schedule a CryptoKeyVersion for
destruction.

Upon calling this method,
CryptoKeyVersion.state will
be set to
DESTROY_SCHEDULED,
and destroy_time will
be set to the time
destroy_scheduled_duration
in the future. At that time, the
state will automatically
change to
DESTROYED,
and the key material will be irrevocably destroyed.

Before the
destroy_time is
reached,
RestoreCryptoKeyVersion
may be called to reverse the process.

snippets.title: cloudkms Encrypt Sample
snippets.description:
Encrypt encrypts data, so that it can only be recovered by a call to
Decrypt. The
CryptoKey.purpose must be
ENCRYPT_DECRYPT.

snippets.title: cloudkms GenerateRandomBytes Sample
snippets.description:
GenerateRandomBytes generate random bytes using the Cloud KMS randomness source in the provided
location.

snippets.title: cloudkms GetCryptoKey Sample
snippets.description:
GetCryptoKey returns metadata for a given CryptoKey, as
well as its primary
CryptoKeyVersion.

snippets.title: cloudkms GetCryptoKeyVersion Sample
snippets.description:
GetCryptoKeyVersion returns metadata for a given
CryptoKeyVersion.

snippets.title: cloudkms GetIamPolicy Sample
snippets.description:
GetIamPolicy gets the access control policy for a resource. Returns an empty policy
if the resource exists and does not have a policy set.

snippets.title: cloudkms GetImportJob Sample
snippets.description: GetImportJob returns metadata for a given ImportJob.

snippets.title: cloudkms GetKeyRing Sample
snippets.description: GetKeyRing returns metadata for a given KeyRing.

snippets.title: cloudkms GetLocation Sample
snippets.description: GetLocation gets information about a location.

snippets.title: cloudkms GetPublicKey Sample
snippets.description:
GetPublicKey returns the public key for the given
CryptoKeyVersion. The
CryptoKey.purpose must be
ASYMMETRIC_SIGN
or
ASYMMETRIC_DECRYPT.

snippets.title: cloudkms ImportCryptoKeyVersion Sample
snippets.description:
ImportCryptoKeyVersion import wrapped key material into a
CryptoKeyVersion.

All requests must specify a CryptoKey. If
a CryptoKeyVersion is additionally
specified in the request, key material will be reimported into that
version. Otherwise, a new version will be created, and will be assigned the
next sequential id within the CryptoKey.

snippets.title: cloudkms ListCryptoKeyVersions Sample
snippets.description: ListCryptoKeyVersions lists CryptoKeyVersions.

snippets.title: cloudkms ListCryptoKeys Sample
snippets.description: ListCryptoKeys lists CryptoKeys.

snippets.title: cloudkms ListImportJobs Sample
snippets.description: ListImportJobs lists ImportJobs.

snippets.title: cloudkms ListKeyRings Sample
snippets.description: ListKeyRings lists KeyRings.

snippets.title: cloudkms ListLocations Sample
snippets.description: ListLocations lists information about the supported locations for this service.

snippets.title: cloudkms MacSign Sample
snippets.description:
MacSign signs data using a CryptoKeyVersion
with CryptoKey.purpose MAC,
producing a tag that can be verified by another source with the same key.

snippets.title: cloudkms MacVerify Sample
snippets.description:
MacVerify verifies MAC tag using a
CryptoKeyVersion with
CryptoKey.purpose MAC, and returns
a response that indicates whether or not the verification was successful.

snippets.title: cloudkms RestoreCryptoKeyVersion Sample
snippets.description:
RestoreCryptoKeyVersion restore a CryptoKeyVersion in the
DESTROY_SCHEDULED
state.

Upon restoration of the CryptoKeyVersion,
state will be set to
DISABLED,
and destroy_time will
be cleared.

snippets.title: cloudkms SetIamPolicy Sample
snippets.description:
SetIamPolicy sets the access control policy on the specified resource. Replaces
any existing policy.

Can return NOT_FOUND, INVALID_ARGUMENT, and PERMISSION_DENIED
errors.

snippets.title: cloudkms TestIamPermissions Sample

resource does not exist, this will return an empty set of
permissions, not a NOT_FOUND error.

Note: This operation is designed to be used for building

snippets.title: cloudkms UpdateCryptoKey Sample
snippets.description: UpdateCryptoKey update a CryptoKey.

snippets.title: cloudkms UpdateCryptoKeyPrimaryVersion Sample
snippets.description:
UpdateCryptoKeyPrimaryVersion update the version of a CryptoKey that
will be used in
Encrypt.

Returns an error if called on a key whose purpose is not
ENCRYPT_DECRYPT.

snippets.title: cloudkms UpdateCryptoKeyVersion Sample
snippets.description:
UpdateCryptoKeyVersion update a CryptoKeyVersion's
metadata.

state may be changed between
ENABLED
and
DISABLED
using this method. See
DestroyCryptoKeyVersion
and
RestoreCryptoKeyVersion
to move between other states.
